Female. Frons and face wider than anterior ocellus width and wider than in male. Cell r 1 entirely brown infuscated (
Fig. 20
). Fore tarsi unicolorous. Tergite 8 (
Figs. 21, 22
) widened laterally, with distinct sulcus distally. Sternite 8 (
